            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Project 2 -->
        <div class="row mb-5">
           <div class="col-md-6">
              <!-- Clickable Image that triggers the modal -->
              <a href="#" data-bs-toggle="modal" data-bs-target="#project2Modal">
                 <img src="UIUX1.PNG" class="img-fluid" alt="Project 2">
              </a>
           </div>
           <div class="col-md-6 d-flex flex-column justify-content-center">
               <h3 id="ds2">Design Works</h3>
               <p id="ds2">
                This is one of the in-class exercises I did. This app is something related to 'Mcdonalds',
                under the food & beverage (f&b) category. This is why I decided to use bright colours, 
                yellow and red, white, which are quite similar to the colors used for the original 'Mcdonalds' app. 
                </p>

                <p>
                This app shows 9 pages in total, the homepage, the deals page, the order page, split into In-Store 
                and Delivery pages, the rewards page, the my account page, meant for each user to review their own 
                personal information, the sign up and log in page, for users who have membership or want to get 
                membership.
                </p>

                <p>
                I made all 9 pages look refreshing so that it would attract users and it also looks structured. 
                Based on the current Mcdonalds app, I also made some changes and added and updated some things to 
                make it much better, such as the rewards page, splitting it into bronze, silver and gold levels. 
                </p>

                <p>
                This helps to attract more users to buy more food & drinks so that they could earn and redeem 
                rewards based on how much food they buy. This depends the level, bronze, silver and gold.
               </p>
           </div>
        </div>

